  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00004_197169_1517807320345&sectionId=27966&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00004_197169_1517807320345
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Prevention of Insults to National Honour`
  line `Act, 1971.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (27967)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Insults to Indian National Flag and Constitution of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00004_197169_1517807320345&sectionId=27967&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00004_197169_1517807320345
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Whoever in any public place or in`
  line `any other place within public view burns, mutilates, defaces, difiles, disfigures, destroys, tramples upon or`
  line `^1[otherwise shows disrespect to or brings] into contempt (whether by words, either spoken or written, or`
  line `by acts) the Indian National Flag or the Constitution of India or any part thereof, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.-- Comments expressing disapprobation or criticism of the Constitution or of the`
  line `Indian National Flag or of any measures of the Government with a view to obtain an amendment of the`
  line `Constitution of India or an alteration of the Indian National Flag by lawful means do not constitute an`
  line `offence under this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--The expression "Indian National Flag" includes any picture, painting, drawing or`
  line `photograph, or other visible representation of the Indian National Flag, or of any part or parts thereof,`
  line `made of any substance or represented on any substance.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.-- The expression "public place" means any place intended for use by, or accessible to,`
  line `the public and Includes any public conveyance.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation 4.--The disrespect to the Indian National Flag means and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) a gross affront or indignity offered to the Indian National Flag; or`
  line
  line `(b) dipping the Indian National Flag in salute to any person or thing; or`
  line
  line `(c) flying the Indian National Flag at half-mast except on occasions on which the Indian National`
  line `Flag is flown at half-mast on public buildings in accordance with the instructions issued by the`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `(d) using the Indian National Flag as a drapery in any form whatsoever except in State funerals or`
  line `armed forces or other para-military forces funerals; or`
  line
  line `^3[(e) using the Indian National Flag,--`
  line
  line `(i) as a portion of costume, uniform or accessory of any description which is worn below the`
  line `waist of any person; or`
  line
  line `(ii) by embroidering or printing it on cushions, handkerchiefs, napkins, undergarments or any`
  line `dress material; or]`
  line
  line `(f) putting any kind of inscription upon the Indian National Flag; or`
  line
  line `(g) using the Indian National Flag as a receptacle for receiving, delivering or carrying anything`
  line `except flower petals before the Indian National Flag is unfurled as part of celebrations on special`
  line `occasions including the Republic Day or the Independence day; or`
  line
  line `(h) using the Indian National Flag as covering for a statute or a monument or a speaker's desk or`
  line `a speaker's platform; or`
  line
  line `(i) allowing the Indian National Flag to touch the ground or the floor or trail in water`
  line `intentionally; or`
  line
  line `(j) draping the Indian National Flag over the hood, top and sides or back or on a vehicle, train,`
  line `boat or an aircraft or any other similar object; or`
  line
  line `(k) using the Indian National Flag as a covering for a building; or`
  line
  line `(l) intentionally displaying the Indian National Flag with the "saffron" down.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 31 of 2003, s. 2, for "otherwise brings" (w.e.f. 8-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2 The Explanation inserted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 51 of 2005, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 20-12-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (27968)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Prevention of singing of Indian National Anthem, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00004_197169_1517807320345&sectionId=27968&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00004_197169_1517807320345
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Whoever Intentionally prevents the`
  line `singing of the Indian National Anthem or causes disturbance to any assembly engaged in such singing`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (27969)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Enhanced penalty on second and subsequent convictions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 31 of 2003, s. 3 (w.e.f. 8-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00004_197169_1517807320345&sectionId=27969&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00004_197169_1517807320345
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[3A. Enhanced penalty on second and subsequent convictions.—Whoever, having already been`
  line `convicted of an offence under section 2 or section 3, is again convicted of any such offence shall be`
  line `punishable for the second and for every subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which shall not`
  line `be less than one year.]`
